name: Gr10
description: The GR10 is a long-distance footpath that runs from the Atlantic Ocean to the Mediterranean Sea, traversing the Pyrenees mountain range in southern France. It is one of the most popular and scenic hiking trails in Europe, known for its stunning landscapes, diverse flora and fauna, and challenging terrain. The trail covers approximately 866 kilometers (538 miles) and typically takes around 50 days to complete, depending on the hiker's pace and chosen route.
